:wip

Importing and Exporting Packages are the way to share projects that have been made with other members of the community. 
How you export actions and command has changed with 0.2.0, now, you can just <Kbd>Right-Click</kbd> on an action, and use the `Add to Export` or `Remove from Export` menu items. 

## Exporting

In the Top Left of Streamer.bot you will see an `Export` button.

![image](https://github.com/Streamerbot/docs/assets/136271820/3209e65f-817c-44ba-863c-297d2b4574c8)

::callout{icon=i-mdi-navigation}
Pressing that will bring up The Export window.
::

The Export window is modeless, which means you can keep it open off to the side, as you add your actions and commands and see it populate.
in 0.2.3 Additional export options have been added: you can now also export [Timed Actions](/triggers/core/timed-actions), [WebSocket Servers](/api/csharp/core/servers-clients#websocket-server), and [WebSocket Clients](/api/csharp/core/servers-clients#websocket-clients). They are added in the same way as actions (<Kbd>Right-Click</kbd> > `Add to Export` or `Remove from Export`).

There is also information you can attach to an export, such as author, description and a version.

![image](https://github.com/Streamerbot/docs/assets/136271820/dd2fb6fb-dc98-447d-89c3-86d55bca2ad2)

`Export to to Clipboard` will copy a string of UUEncoded text to the clipboard and show a confirmation dialogue.

`Export to File` will bring up a Save dialogue and create a file ready for transport.

Exported actions will retain any custom JSON or [C# code](/api/sub-actions/core/csharp/execute-csharp-code) and will retain the [sub-actions](/guide/actions#sub-actions), group names, [Triggers](/guide/triggers), [Commands](/guide/commands), and custom [Queues](/guide/actions#action-queues) an action was associated with. When actions are re-imported, Streamerbot will attempt to rebuild connections with OBS objects that match but these sub-actions may require opening up to confirm they are pointing to te intended sources

## Importing 

Actions, Commands and more can be Imported from other installations of Streamer.bot. They will also properly handle new triggers, as well as updating certain data in old exports to the new trigger system.

![image](https://github.com/Streamerbot/docs/assets/136271820/9d3b5552-5553-43e5-90a7-330d6ba1df4f)

::callout{icon=i-mdi-navigation}
To Import an action, open the Import dialogue by pressing `Import` in the Top Left of Streamer.bot.
::

You can Import 2 ways either paste in the UUEncoded string for the package you want or drag and drop a file with that contains your import code into the top box.

::callout{icon=i-mdi-alert color=amber}
If for some reason you are running streamer.bot with elevated permissions or in Administrator mode, you will be unable to use the drag-drop functionality, unless the Explorer window you are dragging from is also running in Administrator mode.
To work around this you can temporarily load the application in regular mode while importing actions
::

you'll be able to overwrite commands and actions. When you're presented with actions and commands to import, you can right click on an action or a command, and include/exclude it, if its an exact match to an existing action or command, you can also flag it to be overwritten or not.

![image](https://github.com/Streamerbot/docs/assets/136271820/be67b1dc-337d-4170-933c-37d619a402da)
